Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setFPlanMode(25.10)                                        setFPlanMode(25.10)

Name
       setFPlanMode  -  Sets the global parameters of the check floorplan fea-
       ture

Syntax
        setFPlanMode

       [-help] [-reset]

       [-autoSyncMasterClone     {busGuides|constraints|stdcells|macros|route-
       Blockages|placeBlockages}]

       [-cellsForExtraSites <cell_name>]

       [-checkTypes   {basic|fence|oddEvenSiteRow|macroPin|color|alignmentFol-
       lowingPin|alignmentPartitionClone|

       busGuideConnectivity|feedThrough|partitionInPartition|multiLayer-
       Pin|powerDomain|

       partition|place|sameLengthSite|narrowChannel|blockOnly|unifiedVddOnBot-
       tom|tsv|exclusiveGroup|all}]

       [-cutOffPlaceBlockageOutsideDie {true|false}]

       [-cutOffRouteBlockageOutsideDie {true|false}]

       [-defaultBlockageNamePrefix <string>]

       [-defaultPowerDomainSite {true|false}]

       [-defaultRowPatternSite <string>]

       [-defaultTechSite <string>]

       [-enableRectilinearDesign {true|false}]

       [-extraRowPattern <rowPatternName>]

       [-extraSites  <site_name>]

       [-firstRowSiteIndex <int>]

       [-includeIoWhenInitArea {true|false}]

       [-initAllCompatibleCoreSiteRows {true|false}]

       [-keepRowsWhenMovingPowerDomain {true|false}]

       [-lastRowSiteIndex <int>]

       [-maxIoHeight {true|false}]

       [-minimumSites <value>]

       [-move_child_constraint_with_constraint {true|false}]

       [-move_macros_with_constraint {guide|region|fence|none|all}]

       [-move_preplaced_std_cell_only {true|false}]

       [-move_std_cell_with_constraint {guide|region|fence|none|all}]

       [-narrowChannelThreshold <value>]

       [-no_cut_row {true|false}]

       [-powerRailLayer <string>]

       [-rowHeightIncrementCornerToCorner <value>]

       [-rowHeightIncrementIncornerToCorner <value>]

       [-rowHeightIncrementIncornerToIncorner <value>]

       [-rowHeightMultiple <value>]

       [-rowSiteHeight {any|odd|even|computed}]

       [-rowSiteWidth {any|odd|even}]

       [-skipViolations <string>]

       [-snap_all_corners_to_grid {true|false}]

       [-snapBlockGrid         {manufacturing|inst|placement|userDefine|Layer-
       Track|finfetInst|finfetManufacturing|finfetPlacement}]

       [-snapConstraintGrid    {manufacturing|inst|placement|userDefine|Layer-
       Track|finfetInst|finfetManufacturing|finfetPlacement}]

       [-snapCoreGrid {manufacturing|inst|placement|userDefine|LayerTrack|fin-
       fetInst|finfetManufacturing|finfetPlacement}]

       [-snapDieGrid  {manufacturing|inst|placement|userDefine|LayerTrack|fin-
       fetInst|finfetManufacturing|finfetPlacement}]

       [-snapIoGrid   {manufacturing|inst|placement|userDefine|LayerTrack|fin-
       fetInst|finfetManufacturing|finfetPlacement}]

       [-snapPlaceBlockageGrid   {manufacturing|inst|finfetInst|finfetManufac-
       turing|userDefine}]

       [-snapPlaceBlockageType {closest|upsize|sequential}]

       [-user_define_grid {<x_offset y_offset x_pitch y_pitch>}]

       Sets  the  global  parameters  of  the check floorplan feature. Use the
       getFPlanMode command to return the current settings for  the  setFPlan-
       Mode  command.  The  setFPlanMode  parameters  affects the behavior the
       checkFPlan command. You can use this command after importing the design
       and before using the checkFPlan command.

Parameters
       -autoSyncMasterClone {busGuides|constraints|stdcells|macros|routeBlock-
       ages|placeBlockages}
              Specifies the objects that automatically sync up between  master
              and  clone  partitions during add, delete, edit, move, flip, ro-
              tate, unplace, or stretch operations. The sync-up object can  be
              bus guides, standard cells, macros, constraints (fence/guide/re-
              gion of hinsts), placement blockages, or routing blockages.

              * busGuides:  Any  change  (add, delete, edit, move, or stretch)
                for busGuides in master will sync-up to other hinsts that have
                the same module.

                For example, setFPlanMode -autoSyncMasterClone {busGuides}

              * constraints: Any change (move, reshape,  create,  unplace)  in
                hinsts constraints of master will sync-up to other hinsts that
                have the same module.

                * When constraints is not specified, tool will not sync-up any
                  change of fence/guide/region between master and clones.

                * When  constraints  is  specified, tool will auto sync-up any
                  change of fence/guide/region between master and clones  when
                  doing moving/stretching.

              * stdcells:  Any change (move) in standard cells will sync-up to
                other hinsts that have the same module.

                For example, setFPlanMode -autoSyncMasterClone {stdcells}

              * macros: Any change (move, flip, rotate, or  unplace)  in  hard
                macros  in  master  will sync-up to other hinsts that have the
                same module.

                For example, setFPlanMode -autoSyncMasterClone {macro}

              * placeBlockages: Any change (add, delete, edit, move,  reshape)
                in  placement blockages will sync-up to other hinsts that have
                the same module.

              * routeBlockages: Any change (add, delete, edit, move,  reshape)
                in  routing  blockages  will sync-up to other hinsts that have
                the same module.

              Default: " "

              Data_type:  enums={busGuides constraints stdcells macros  place-
              Blockages routeBlockages}_list

       -cellsForExtraSites <cell_name>
              Specifies  the cell names for which the additional sites will be
              created. These sites can be used up later in the flow.

              Default: " "

              Data_type: string

       -checkTypes {basic|fence|oddEvenSiteRow|macroPin|color|alignmentFollow-
       ingPin|alignmentPartitionClone|

              busGuideConnectivity|feedThrough|partitionInPartition|multiLay-
              erPin|powerDomain|partition|place|

              sameLengthSite|narrowChannel|blockOnly|unifiedVddOnBot-
              tom|tsv|exclusiveGroup|all}" Specifies the check types  for  the
              checkFPlan command.

              *

                * basic:  Checks  the basic quality of the floorplan to detect
                  potential problems before the design is passed on  to  other
                  tools.

                * fence: Checks the fences.

                * oddEvenSiteRow:  Checks  odd  or even site row. It checks if
                  the  current  row  fits  to  the  setting  of   setFPlanMode
                  -rowSiteWidth and -rowSiteHeight.

                * macroPin: Checks if the macro pins are off track.

                  Note:  The  checkFPlan command verifies macro pins only when
                  the block snap rule is set to the LayerTrack grid (setFPlan-
                  Mode -snapBlockGrid LayerTrack).

                * color: Checks the color issues  of  all  floorplan  objects,
                  such as pins, preRoutes, prePlacedInst, etc.

                * alignmentFollowingPin:  Checks if the centerline of the fol-
                  lowpin is the same as the row's border and matches the power
                  attribute.

                * alignmentPartitionClone: Checks that  partition  clones  are
                  aligned  with  their  master  on the power mesh. This checks
                  that the master and clones  partitions  are  inside  a  core
                  boundary,  and  ensures  that  the partition fence instances
                  sizes match the master instance.

                * busGuideConnectivity: Checks incorrect overlapping and  con-
                  nectivity.

                * feedThrough: Checks feedthrough buffer insertion.

                * partitionInPartition:  Checks if child partitions reside in-
                  side parent partitions.

                * multiLayerPin: Checks multi layer pins.

                * powerDomain: Checks the power domains.

                * partition: Checks the partitions.

                * place: Checks the placement.

                * sameLengthSite: Checks the same length site rule where, in a
                  group of continuous poly stripes with the same  length,  the
                  number  of  sites must be >= N.(N is specified by the -mini-
                  mumSites option.)

                * narrowChannel: Checks for narrow channels.

                * blockOnly: Checks for performance most  frequently  used  in
                  block   implementation.   Includes:  basic,  oddEvenSiteRow,
                  macroPin, and color.

                * unifiedVddOnBottom: Checks whether all the cells in the  de-
                  sign are with the same vdd on bottom.

                * tsv: Checks the TSV placement.

                * exclusiveGroup: Checks exclusive group region spacing.

                * all:  Performs  all checks on the floorplan to detect poten-
                  tial problems before the design is passed on to other tools.

              Default: basic

              Data_type:  enums={basic  fence  oddEvenSiteRow  macroPin  color
              alignmentFollowingPin alignmentPartitionClone busGuideConnectiv-
              ity  feedThrough  partitionInPartition multiLayerPin powerDomain
              partition place sameLengthSite narrowChannel blockOnly  unified-
              VddOnBottom tsv all}_list

       -cutOffPlaceBlockageOutsideDie {true|false}
              When  creating  placement blockages, it cuts the part outside of
              die and snaps it by default.

              Default: true

              Data_type: bool

       -cutOffRouteBlockageOutsideDie {true|false}
              When creating routing blockages around inst/Hinst/Partition,  it
              cuts  the  part  outside of die and snaps it by default. If this
              option is set to false, then the outside part  is  not  cut  and
              snapped.

              Default: true

              Data_type: bool

       -defaultBlockageNamePrefix <string>
              Specifies  the  name  prefix  for placement blockage and routing
              blockage.

              Default: " "

              Data_type: string

       -defaultPowerDomainSite {true | false }
              Creates rows based on the default power domain site  instead  of
              the the default site of the design.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -defaultRowPatternSite <string>
              Specifies the default ROWPATTERN site.

              Note:  Defined  in the LEF, a ROWPATTERN site is a set of previ-
              ously defined sites and their orientations. This site is defines
              a placement site in the design.

              Default: " "

              Data_type: string

       -defaultTechSite <string>
              Specifies a site as default technical site.

              Note: After setting a default technical site, the auto-calculat-
              ing default-technical-site functionality is disabled.

              Note: The saveFPlan, loadFPlan, initCoreRow and checkFPlan  com-
              mands honor the default technical site specified using the setF-
              PlanMode -defaultTechSite parameter.

              Default: auto-calculated default-technical-site by tool.

              Data_type: string

       -enableRectilinearDesign {true | false}
              Specifies  whether  the design boundary can be changed to recti-
              linear shape.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -extraRowPattern <rowPatternName>
              Specifies the ROWPATTERN name to create. You can also specify  a
              ROWPATTERN list.

              Note:

              * The initCoreRow command creates rows for the specified ROWPAT-
                TERN sites.

              * The  ROWPATTERN should be defined in LEF file. The initCoreRow
                command creates rows from core bottom edge as the defined  or-
                der and orientation of all sites.

              * The  -extraRowPattern  parameter does not support the creation
                of extra row pattern for non-default power domains.

              Default: " "

              Data_type: string

       -extraSites  <site_name>
              Specifies the name for the additional sites that will be created
              for cells which are not used in the netlist  by  default.  These
              sites can be used up later in the flow.

              Note:  Sites  for  all  specified cells should be defined in the
              LEF.

              Default: " "

              Data_type: string

       -firstRowSiteIndex <int>
              Specifies the index number in default row site  pattern  as  the
              first row for creating hybrid rows.

              For example,

              Default: 0

              Data_type: int

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each setFPlanMode parameter. For a detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command:

               man setFPlanMode.

       -includeIoWhenInitArea {true|false}
              Includes IO cells when calculating the area of modules.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -initAllCompatibleCoreSiteRows {true|false}
              When enabled, initCoreRow creates SITES which are  used  by  all
              cells in the library.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -keepRowsWhenMovingPowerDomain {true|false}
              Specifies whether to keep all existing rows in power domain when
              moving,  resizing  or reshaping a power domain on GUI or by com-
              mand.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -lastRowSiteIndex <int>
              Specifies the index number in default row site  pattern  as  the
              last row for creating hybrid rows.

              Default: -1

              Data_type: int

       -maxIoHeight {true|false}
              When specified, the maximum IO height is used to calculate a die
              box  with  IO  placement.  By  default, the minimum IO height is
              used.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -minimumSites <value>
              Specifies the number of minimal sites (N)  that  the  checkFPlan
              command will check for the same length site rule. When the same-
              LengthSite  option  of  the  -checkTypes parameter is specified,
              this parameter is required.

              Default: 0

              Data_type: int

       -move_child_constraint_with_constraint {true|false}
              Specifies that the child constraints should move with the parent
              constraint modules at the same time.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -move_macros_with_constraint {guide|region|fence|none|all}
              Specifies that the macros move with the  constraint  modules  at
              the same time.

              Default: fence

              Data_type: enums={guide region fence none all}_list

       -move_preplaced_std_cell_only {true|false}
              Specifies  that only the pre-placed standard cells can move with
              the constraint modules at the same time.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -move_std_cell_with_constraint {guide|region|fence|none|all}
              Specifies that standard cells move with the  constraint  modules
              at the same time.

              Default: none

              Data_type: enums={guide region fence none all}_list

       -narrowChannelThreshold <value>
              Reports  the  narrow channels whose width (in micros) is smaller
              than the specified value. When the narrowChannel option  of  the
              -checkTypes parameter is specified, this parameter is required.

              Default: 0

              Data_type: float

       -no_cut_row {true|false}
              Specifies  that the rows are not required to be cut before other
              operations. The following commands honor this mode setting:

              * createRouteBlkAlongTrack

              * check_ufc

              * fix_floorplan

              * finishFloorplan

              * check_tcic

              With the -no_cut_row parameter set to false  or  not  specified,
              the tool will run above the mentioned commands based on the cur-
              rent row shape. So the rows for objects like insts, place block-
              ages are expected to be cut out before running these commands to
              get expected results.

              If  rows  are  not cut before run these commands are run and the
              -no_cut_row parameter is set to true, the tool will identify the
              rows that have not been cut before running  these  commands.  It
              calls  the  cutRow  command  to get a cut row shape during these
              commands action. The cutRow command cuts  the  rows  for  insts,
              hinsts, place blockages, route blockages, power domains, groups,
              or  bumps  by default. These commands will work based on the cut
              row shape. But the actual row shape is not changed  after  these
              operations.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -powerRailLayer <string>
              Specifies  the  layers  used for calculating the power/ground on
              the bottom attribute of the cell or techsite.  By  default,  the
              lowest metal layer is used.

              Default: " "

              Data_type: string

       -reset Restores all parameters modified using setFPlanMode to their de-
              fault settings. The -reset parameter must be the first parameter
              specified.  If you specify -reset by itself, the software resets
              all setFPlanMode parameters to  their  default  values.  If  you
              specify  parameters after -reset, the software resets only those
              parameters to their default values.

              Any values that do not already match the default value  and  are
              reset will be reported.

       -rowHeightIncrementCornerToCorner <CornerToCornerValue>
              Specifies  the  offset  value  for  user defined row height con-
              straint with corner to corner edge.

              Default: 0

              Data_type: int

       -rowHeightIncrementIncornerToCorner <I> <ncornerToCornerValue>
              Specifies the offset value for  user  defined  row  height  con-
              straint with incorner to corner edge.

              Default: 0

              Data_type: int

       -rowHeightIncrementIncornerToIncorner <IncornerToIncornerValue>
              Specifies  the  offset  value  for  user defined row height con-
              straint with incorner to incorner edge.

              Default: 0

              Data_type: int

       -rowHeightMultiple <multipleHeightValue>
              Specifies the pitch value  for  user  defined  row  height  con-
              straint.

              Default: 0

              Data_type: int

       -rowSiteHeight {any|odd|even|computed}
              Specifies the odd, even, or user defined row height constraints.

              Note:  For  a hybrid row design, specify the computed option for
              the -rowSiteHeight parameter to specify the row constraints.

              Default: any

              Data_type: enums={any odd even computed}

       -rowSiteWidth {any|odd|even}
              Specifies the odd even row width constraints.

              Data_type: enums={any odd even}

       -skipViolations <string>
              Skips reporting and showing the violation(s) associated with the
              specified message ID(s) in the violation browser.

              Note: You can specify a list of message IDs with the -skipViola-
              tions parameter. It also supports wildcards.

              * If the -skipViolations parameter is not  specified,  the  tool
                reports  all  the violations checked by the checkFPlan command
                in the terminal/.log/.logv and shows  them  in  the  violation
                browser if there is marker box.

              * If  the  -skipViolations parameter is specified, the tool does
                not report the violations in terminal/.log/.logv and also does
                not show them in the violation browser even through  there  is
                marker box.

              For  example,  the  following command does not report the viola-
              tions for IMPFP-7236.

              setFPlanMode -checkTypes basic -skipViolations IMPFP-7236

              checkFPlan

              Default: " "

              Data_type: string

       -snap_all_corners_to_grid {true|false}
              Snaps all corners of an object to the grid. It defines the snap-
              ping behavior for the kinds of objects: constraint,  ptnCut  and
              black box.

              Note:  This option only works when the snapping grid is user de-
              fined grid or FinFET grid.

              * When the snapping  grid  is  ManufactureGrid,  the  object  is
                snapped to the closest grid.

              * When  the snapping grid is InstanceGrid and PlacementGrid, the
                object is moved to first snap the LL corner to the closest lo-
                cation and then to snap the UR corner to closest location.

              * When the snapping grid is user defined  grid,  the  object  is
                moved  to  snap the LL corner to the closest location. Then if
                the -snap_all_corners_to_grid parameter set to true,  the  ob-
                ject is moved to snap the UR corner to the closest location.

              * When  the  snapping grid is FinFET grid and the -snap_all_cor-
                ners_to_grid parameter set to true, all corners of the  object
                are   snapped   to   the   closest   grid.   However,  if  the
                -snap_all_corners_to_grid parameter set to false, only the  LL
                corner of the object is snapped to the closest location.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -snapBlockGrid {manufacturing | inst | placement | userDefine | Layer-
       Track | finfetInst | finfetManufacturing | finfetPlacement }
              Specifies the block snap rules. It can be set to snap to:

              * manufacturing: Manufacture Grid

              * inst: Instance Grid

              * placement: Placement Grid

              * userDefine: User-define Grid

              * LayerTrack: LayerTrack Grid

              * finfetManufacturing: FinFET Manufacture Grid

              * finfetInst: FinFET Instance Grid

              * finfetPlacement: FinFET Placement Grid

              Default: manufacturing

              Note: For FinFET designs, the default is finfetManufacturing.

              Data_type: enums={manufacturing inst placement userDefine Layer-
              Track finfetInst finfetManufacturing finfetPlacement}

       -snapConstraintGrid {manufacturing | inst | placement | userDefine |
       LayerTrack | finfetInst | finfetManufacturing | finfetPlacement }
              Specify the constraint snap rules. It can be set to snap to:

              * manufacturing: Manufacture Grid

              * inst: Instance Grid

              * placement: Placement Grid

              * userDefine: User-define Grid

              * LayerTrack: LayerTrack Grid

              * finfetManufacturing: FinFET Manufacture Grid

              * finfetInst: FinFET Instance Grid

              * finfetPlacement: FinFET Placement Grid

              Default: inst

              Note: For FinFET designs, the default is finfetInst.

              Data_type: enums={manufacturing inst placement userDefine Layer-
              Track finfetInst finfetManufacturing finfetPlacement}

       -snapCoreGrid {manufacturing | inst | placement | userDefine | Layer-
       Track | finfetInst | finfetManufacturing | finfetPlacement }
              Specifies the core snap rules. It can be set to snap to:

              * manufacturing: Manufacture Grid

              * inst: Instance Grid

              * placement: Placement Grid

              * userDefine: User-define Grid

              * LayerTrack: LayerTrack Grid

              * finfetManufacturing: FinFET Manufacture Grid

              * finfetInst: FinFET Instance Grid

              * finfetPlacement: FinFET Placement Grid

              Default: placement

              Note: For FinFET designs, the default is finfetPlacement.

              Data_type: enums={manufacturing inst placement userDefine Layer-
              Track finfetInst finfetManufacturing finfetPlacement}

       -snapDieGrid {manufacturing | inst | placement | userDefine | Layer-
       Track | finfetInst | finfetManufacturing | finfetPlacement }
              Specifies the die snap rules. It can be set to snap to:

              * manufacturing: Manufacture Grid

              * inst: Instance Grid

              * placement: Placement Grid

              * userDefine: User-define Grid

              * LayerTrack: LayerTrack Grid

              * finfetManufacturing: FinFET Manufacture Grid

              * finfetInst: FinFET Instance Grid

              * finfetPlacement: FinFET Placement Grid

              Default: placement

              Note: For FinFET designs, the default is finfetPlacement.

              Data_type: enums={manufacturing inst placement userDefine Layer-
              Track finfetInst finfetManufacturing finfetPlacement}

       -snapIoGrid {manufacturing | inst | placement | userDefine | LayerTrack
       | finfetInst | finfetManufacturing | finfetPlacement }
              Specifies the IO snap rules. It can be set to snap to:

              * manufacturing: Manufacture Grid

              * inst: Instance Grid

              * placement: Placement Grid

              * userDefine: User-define Grid

              * LayerTrack: LayerTrack Grid

              * finfetManufacturing: FinFET Manufacture Grid

              * finfetInst: FinFET Instance Grid

              * finfetPlacement: FinFET Placement Grid

              Default: manufacturing

              Note: For FinFET designs, the default is finfetManufacturing.

              Data_type: enums={manufacturing inst placement userDefine Layer-
              Track finfetInst finfetManufacturing finfetPlacement}

       -snapPlaceBlockageGrid {manufacturing|inst|finfetInst|finfetManufactur-
       ing|userDefine}
              Specifies the placement blockage snap rules.

              * manufacturing: Manufacture Grid

              * inst: Instance Grid

              * userDefine: User-define Grid

              * finfetManufacturing: FinFET Manufacture Grid

              * finfetInst: FinFET Instance Grid

              Default: inst

              Data_type:  enums={manufacturing  inst finfetInst finfetManufac-
              turing userDefine}

       -snapPlaceBlockageType {closest|upsize|sequential}
              Specifies a snapping type for placement blockages. The  snapping
              types can be:

              * closest:  The tool snaps all corners of the placement blockage
                to the closest specified grid, regardless of  which  direction
                could increase or decrease the blockage size.

              * upsize:  The  tool snaps all corners of the placement blockage
                to the corresponding closest specified grid in  the  direction
                which would increase the objects' size.

              * sequential:  The tool moves the placement blockage to snap the
                low-left corner to the closest specified grid, then snaps  the
                upper-right corner to the closest grid.

              This setting is honored by the following commands:

              * setObjFPlanBox

              * setObjFPlanBoxList

              * setObjFPlanPolygon

              * createPlaceBlockage {-box|-boxList|-polygon}

              * snapFPlan -placeBlk

              Default: closest

              Data_type: enums={closest upsize sequential}

       -user_define_grid {<x_offset y_offset x_pitch y_pitch>}
              Specifies the user-defined grid.

              The format is {<x_offset y_offset x_pitch y_pitch>}.

              Where,

              <x_offset y_offset> is the offset of the user-defined grid.

              <x_pitch> separates the vertical grid lines.

              <y_pitch> separates the horizontal grid lines.

              Note: The values are in microns.

              Default: {0 0 0 0}

              Data_type: box

Examples
       In  the  following,  the  command checks the same length site rule in a
       group of continuous poly stripes with the same length.  The  number  of
       minimal sites it check is set to 6 using the -minimumSites parameter.

       setFPlanMode -checkTypes sameLengthSite -minimumSites 6

